You are working on TripRadar AI, a travel planning assistant. Your job is to build beautiful, consistent, dynamic, and responsive user interfaces based on backend-driven logic and user/group preferences. 

Ensure pages (Dashboard, Discover, Trips, Profile, Billing, Notification, Settings) fully support dark/light themes with shared design consistency.

Each page should:
- Load user or group preferences if needed.
- Fetch backend-driven schema when rendering dynamic forms.
- Support animations in both white and black themes.
- Prevent duplication or misalignment of components (e.g., headers, footers, menus).
- Include fallback UX when no data is returned (empty states).

Your responses should include all necessary components and match the user-defined design system.